race.comment: SIGIRIYA ROCK (8) did enough first up at Sale over 1427m, settling midfield and battling away well for fifth. He should be much fitter for that and did tackle some top races last time in, fifth to Evaporate at Randwick second up last time in. Suited to this trip now and can win. SHINY NEW DEEL (1) broke through for a smart win at Sandown Hillside last time out over 1800m. Shinn sticks with him and he draws for options. Rates highly. SAVILLA (3) has won 2/3 this time in, dominant at Mornington last time out. There's more depth here but she can roll forward and go close. EMPHASIZE (4) might be an improver over more ground now at peak fitness.
